    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "## Problem\n\n(This may technically be a \"bug\" in fzf-lua, but tracking it here for reference, and to see if we can mitigate it.)\n\nWhen a `BufWinEnter` handler (and maybe others) shows an error message, ui2 and/or fzf-lua gets confused. fzf-lua throws an error, when presumably ui2 tries to display.\n\nI noticed this with `nvim -V1` ('verbose'), which prints messages when autocmds fail.\n\n```\n[Fzf-lua] fn_selected threw an error: .../site/pack/core/opt/fzf-lua/lua/fzf-lua/win/backdrop.lua:30: Lua: nvim_exec2()[1]..BufWinEnter Autocommands for \"*\": Vim(if):E495: No autocommand file name to substitute for \"<afile>\"\nstack traceback:\n\t[C]: at 0x010128ad38\n\t[builtin#36]: at 0x0101074324\n\t...are/nvim/site/pack/core/opt/fzf-lua/lua/fzf-lua/core.lua:296: in function <...are/nvim/site/pack/core/opt/fzf-lua/lua/fzf-lua/core.lua:262>\n\t...hare/nvim/site/pack/core/opt/fzf-lua/lua/fzf-lua/cmd.lua:38: in function 'run_command'\n\t...share/nvim/site/pack/core/opt/fzf-lua/plugin/fzf-lua.lua:11: in function <...share/nvim/site/pack/core/opt/fzf-lua/plugin/fzf-lua.lua:9>\n\t[C]: in function 'nvim_exec2'\n\tvim/_core/editor.lua: in function 'cmd'\n\t/Users/justin/.config/nvim/init.lua:521: in function </Users/justin/.config/nvim/init.lua:519>\nstack traceback:\n\t[C]: in function 'nvim_open_win0'\n\t.../site/pack/core/opt/fzf-lua/lua/fzf-lua/win/backdrop.lua:30: in function 'open'\n\t...hare/nvim/site/pack/core/opt/fzf-lua/lua/fzf-lua/win.lua:684: in function 'set_backdrop'\n\t...hare/nvim/site/pack/core/opt/fzf-lua/lua/fzf-lua/win.lua:1049: in function 'create'\n\t...are/nvim/site/pack/core/opt/fzf-lua/lua/fzf-lua/core.lua:369: in function 'fzf'\n\t...are/nvim/site/pack/core/opt/fzf-lua/lua/fzf-lua/core.lua:280: in function <...are/nvim/site/pack/core/opt/fzf-lua/lua/fzf-lua/core.lua:278>\n\t[C]: in function 'xpcall'\n\t...are/nvim/site/pack/core/opt/fzf-lua/lua/fzf-lua/core.lua:278: in function <...are/nvim/site/pack/core/opt/fzf-lua/lua/fzf-lua/core.lua:273>\n```\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\n- The code below is a full repro. \n- Note that it defines a `autocmd BufWinEnter * call expand('<afile>')` handler which will show an error with `-V1`.\n    - An alternative, without `-V1`, is to define a handler that calls `:echoerr`: `autocmd BufWinEnter * echoerr 'foo'\"`\n\n```\nNVIM_APPNAME=bug-ui2-fzflua nvim +\"lua vim.pack.add{'https://github.com/ibhagwan/fzf-lua'}\"\n\n# restart with `-V1`\nNVIM_APPNAME=bug-ui2-fzflua nvim -V1 +\"autocmd BufWinEnter * call expand('<afile>')\" +\"lua require('vim._core.ui2').enable({msg={target='cmd'}})\" +\"lua vim.pack.add{'https://github.com/ibhagwan/fzf-lua'}\" +\"lua require('fzf-lua').setup{}\"\n\n# Show the fzf picker. ui2 shows an error, screen goes blank.\n:FzfLua files\n```\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nScreen should not be blank. ui2 should show messages/errors like normal, without otherwise interfering or confusing plugins.\n\nWorkaround: \n\n- open a new (e.g. `:tabnew`) and the screen recovers. \n- returning to the old tab still shows a (mostly) blank layout.\n\n## System info\n\n- Nvim version (nvim -v): `v0.12.0-dev-2713 g925e9e87222c` neovim/neovim@925e9e87222c\n- Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?: n/a\n- Operating system/version: Darwin 24.6.0\n- Terminal name/version: ghostty 1.3.1\n- $TERM environment variable: `xterm-ghostty`\n- Installation: src\n\n",
