            "body": "Not sure if this a similar issue:\n`nvim --clean --cmd \"lua require('vim._core.ui2').enable({})\" --cmd \"au BufEnter * echoerr 1\" src/nvim/main.c +e`\n\nThen type `g<`, the error happened inside ui2, since ui2 is interrupted, its behavior become unreliable: \n```\nError in BufEnter Autocommands for \"*\":                                                                                                  \n1                                                                                                                                        \n1                                                                                                                                        \nvim.schedule callback: runtime/lua/vim/_core/ui2/messages.lua:601: BufEnter Autocommands for \"*\": Vim(echoerr):1 [+3]\n```",
