            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> the error happened inside ui2, since ui2 is interrupted, its behavior become unreliable:\n\nThe thing is that that's not really true. I don't think an autocommand callback erroring should prevent execution of, and report as if an error happened inside, the callback that triggered the autocommand? \n\nIf we can't change that I guess UI2 just needs to `pcall` everything it does.",
